Description: Egypt striken by the plagues sent by God; in the foreground, people carrying a dead body, others mourning a dead woman Etching
Curator's comments: Plate 2 from a series of eleven representing the story of Moses; the numbering was added in the second state and does not match the order of the events as related in the Bible. Undescribed state, with the number, but without the name of any publisher.
Bibliographic references: IFF / Inventaire du Fonds Français: Bibliothèque Nationale, Département des Estampes (29) (undescribed state)
